President Obama spoke with Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan about increasing cooperation in the fight against ISIL. They condemned the recent terrorist attack in Ankara and expressed solidarity in the face of security threats. They also discussed the need to put military pressure on ISIL and support moderate opposition in Syria. Additionally, they emphasized the importance of ending PKK attacks in Turkey and expressed support for a negotiated settlement in Cyprus. They also discussed the agenda for the upcoming G-20 Summit in Turkey.